The City of Johannesburg has uncovered theft&sbquo; fraud and corruption amounting to more than R7.5m at Joburg Market.The report details how three officials at the market&sbquo; together with suppliers&sbquo; allegedly defrauded the city by inflating the number of goods received via the market&rsquo;s procurement processes."The city has opened a case of fraud&sbquo; theft and corruption against all implicated officials and suppliers with the Hawks. The arrest of all those implicated is imminent&sbquo;" said mayor Herman Mashaba.The three implicated officials have been suspended.TMG Digital